    <div class="col-md-6">
      <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span> How this sample app works</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>This app was deployed to Temploy, either using Git or by using <a href="https://github.com/temploy/ruby-getting-started">Temploy Button</a> on the repository.</li>

        <li>When Temploy received the source code, it fetched all the dependencies in the <a href="https://github.com/temploy/ruby-getting-started/blob/main/Gemfile">Gemfile</a>, creating a deployable slug.</li>
        <li>The platform then spins up a dyno, a lightweight container that provides an isolated environment in which the slug can be mounted and executed.</li>
        <li>You can scale your app, manage it, and deploy over <a href="https://addons.temploy.com/">150 add-on services</a>, from the Dashboard or CLI.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
