        <li>If you deployed this app by deploying the Temploy Button, then in a command line shell, run:</li>
        <ul>
          <li><code>git clone https://github.com/temploy/ruby-getting-started.git</code> - this will create a local copy of the source code for the app</li>
          <li><code>cd ruby-getting-started</code> - change directory into the local source code repository</li>
          <li><code>temploy git:remote -a &lt;your-app-name></code> - associate the Temploy app with the repository</li>
          <li>You'll now be set up to run the app locally, or <a href="https://devcenter.temploy.com/articles/getting-started-with-ruby#push-local-changes">deploy changes</a> to Temploy</li>
